==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Appellatively
<hw>Ap*pel"la*tive*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>After the manner of
nouns appellative; in a manner to express whole classes or species;
<as>as, Hercules is sometimes used <ex>appellatively</ex>, that is, as a
common name, to signify a strong man</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Appellativeness</ent>⟦br⟧
